vCloud Powershell function library for VMware's vCloud API.

THIS WILL SOON BE DEPRECATED!

SEE THIS POST: http://geekafterfive.com/2011/09/06/vmware-vcloud-powercli-snapin/

Installation

1. Download the .ps1 (or zip file) from GitHub and place in the folder of your choice.
2. Import the functions using "dot-sourcing" like so:

	. .\vcloud-functions.ps1

3. Profit!


The Functions

Current "cmdlets" are:

Connect-vCloud
Delete-vCloudURI
Deploy-vCloudvApp
Disconnect-vCloud
Get-vCloudCatalog
Get-vCloudConsole
Get-vCloudMedia
Get-vCloudNetwork
Get-vCloudOrg
Get-vCloudURI
Get-vCloudvApp
Get-vCloudvAppTemplate
Get-vCloudvDC
Get-vCloudVM
Post-vCloudURI
PowerOff-vCloudvApp
PowerOff-vCloudVM
PowerOn-vCloudvApp
PowerOn-vCloudVM
Undeploy-vCloudvApp


HELP!

For help on using the functions:

	get-help <cmdlet>
